      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne, ¶ 7/7/84. ¶ J. H. Maiden Esqr, ¶ Secretary to the technologic Museum, ¶ Sydney....</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.07.07a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Maiden</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MRS 202/33/540, Curator, inwards correspondence, 1884, Powerhouse Museum, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS is stamped and annotated '<seg>THE TECHNOLOGICAL MUSEUM | SYDNEY | No. </seg>540<seg> | </seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">RECEIVED | JULY 10 1884</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; "> | Ansd. 14/7'. '</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">SUBMITTED | JLY 29 1884 | TO THE TRUSTEES</seg>
                     <seg style="color: #000000; ">'. </seg>
                  </p>
               </note>Melbourne,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">7/7/84.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">J. H. Maiden Esqr,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Secretary to the technologic Museum,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In accordance with the resolution of the trustees of your institution, to secure the duplicate-collection of the wood-books available here, I beg now to forward this collection, comprising 42 species, 35 of which represent N. S. Wales timber.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; margin-left: 0.3299in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3299in; "
                     xml:lang="en">For the contents of the collection, see J. Maiden to M, 31 July 1884 (in this edition as 84-07-31b).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As these samples were prepared for Victoria, they bear in many instances the notation of this colony; but should you prefer, to have them labelled N.S.W., any book-binder there could readily make the alteration.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>As stated in my former letter<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Maiden, 2 June 1884.</p>
               </note> 6/ each is the cash-expense for shaping the wood in bookform, getting it polished and labelled; so the wood itself is a donation from my Department. You will observe, that the portion, corresponding to leaves in books, has been left unpolished, by which means the grain of the timber can be studied as of simply planed samples.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Perhaps you may deem it expedient, to follow up the forming of such a collection (as I do here) when opportunities in future arise, the idea being, to have quite a library prepared of such imitation-books from wood samples of all parts of the globe.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I remain, dear Mr Maiden, with best regards your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See J. Maiden to M, 14 July 1884 (in this edition as 84-07-14a).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
         </div>
